text: Net2Phone is allowed by the University firewall
AIM chat and file transfering is allowed by the University firewall
SSH is allowed by the University firewall
You may not run any services (e.g., FTP services,listservers,P2P file sharing servers, publishing files via generic file services, etc.) via ResNet or NYURoam wireless networks
The system will trigger an overuse notification if the average for either inbound or outbound usage exceeds 10 GB per week
Currently, the University of Illinois does not have any rate limits set in place
ACT/IT Infrastructure monitors traffic on the network for the purpose of maintaining proper network function
Internet is limited to 3 Mbps per host
Sorenson Videophone 200 is allowed by the University firewall
IMAP and secure IMAP are allowed by the University firewall
Students have a quota of 5 GB per day The quota is reset at 6am
Students data limit is 100 GB per week
